---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Week &amp; Sabbath — The Lunar Sabbath, the Perpetual Sign, and Rome's Imposition | Nazaryah"
  description="The Sabbath cycle Yahuah set at creation resets with the new moon — four Sabbaths every lunar month. The perpetual sign He called olam. And the continuous Roman planetary week that buried both."
>
  <main class="cf-index">

    <div class="cf-index-inner">

      <a href="/calendar" class="cf-index-back"><span class="arrow">←</span><span>Back to the Calendar</span></a>

      <header class="cf-index-header">
        <p class="cf-index-eyebrow">— Category IV &middot; The Week &amp; Sabbath —</p>
        <h1 class="cf-index-title">The Week &amp; Sabbath</h1>
        <p class="cf-index-subtitle">The Sabbath cycle Yahuah set in motion at creation, the perpetual sign He called <em>olam</em>, and the continuous Roman week that buried both for nearly two thousand years.</p>
      </header>

      <section class="cf-studies-grid">

        <a href="/calendar/the-week/sabbath-resets-with-moon" class="cf-study">
          <p class="cf-study-num">Study 1</p>
          <h3>The Sabbath Cycle Resets With the Moon</h3>
          <p>The Sabbath does not float on a never-resetting seven-day rotation. The cycle resets with each new moon — four Sabbaths every lunar month, falling on the 8th, 15th, 22nd, and 29th. The calendar a castaway could keep, anchored to what Yahuah Himself hung in the heavens.</p>
          <span class="cf-study-cta">Read the Study →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/the-week/sabbath-perpetual-sign" class="cf-study">
          <p class="cf-study-num">Study 2</p>
          <h3>A Perpetual Sign</h3>
          <p>Yahuah used the word <em>olam</em> three times in Exodus 31 — the same word that describes Him. The Sabbath is the identifying mark of His people, anchored to creation itself, set apart before Israel existed, and explicitly extended to foreigners in Isaiah 56.</p>
          <span class="cf-study-cta">Read the Study →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/the-week/continuous-week-roman-imposition" class="cf-study">
          <p class="cf-study-num">Study 3</p>
          <h3>The Continuous Week — Rome's Imposition</h3>
          <p>The Sabbath modern Christians keep is not the Sabbath Yahushua kept. The continuous Roman planetary week severed the Sabbath from the moon, Constantine layered Sunday on top in 321 AD, and the Council of Laodicea anathematized anyone who refused to comply.</p>
          <span class="cf-study-cta">Read the Study →</span>
        </a>

      </section>

    </div>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .cf-index {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0e0905 0%, #1a110a 25%, #160f07 100%);
    color: #b8a584;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 4.5rem 1.5rem 6rem;
  }

  .cf-index-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }

  .cf-index-back {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8a7855;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.9rem 0.5rem 0.65rem;
    border: 1px solid #2a1a08;
    background: rgba(10, 6, 2, 0.4);
    font-weight: 600;
